Package seq_loop
-----------------------------------------------
Description: This package aims to accomplish the tasks in Assignment 2.3 of analyzing timing of communication between ROS2 nodes.

Building instructions: Place folder in src. Build normally via colcon build.

*****Node: seq05*****
Input:
/loop05_out
        Type: std_msgs/msg/UInt64

Output:
/seq05_out
        Type: std_msgs/msg/UInt64
        
*****Node: loop05*****
Input:
/loop05_out
        Type: std_msgs/msg/UInt64

Output:
/seq05_out
        Type: std_msgs/msg/UInt64
	
Run:
	ros2 launch seq_loop seq_loop.launch.py 
	# Output file is saved in the directory with the python file to plot,
	python3 plot_results.py
	# Change parameters during runtime 
	ros2 param set /seq05 depth 5

Parameters:
	reliability: [string] reliability policy used by QoS
	durability: [string] durability policy used by QoS
	history: [string] history policy used by QoS
	depth: [int] Length of buffer used by QoS, if history is "keep_last"
	
Core components: 
	timerCallback(): Runs the controller periodically for a sequence of setpoints or stops the robot if finished.
	sequenceController(): Differential Drive proportional controller from X,Y target to left and right wheel speeds.
	objectController(): Differential Drive proportional controller to track object in camera view.
	publishCmd(): Sends the wheel speeds to the relbol_simulator node in proper structure.
	parametersCallback(): Manages changes to parameters during runtime
